<TITLE> JMB chief Saidur arrested </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 25 (bdnews24.com)Chief of banned Islamist outfit Jamaatul Mujahideen Bangladesh Saidur Rahman has been arrested at Dania, Jurain in the capital, the police chief said. Inspector general of police Nur Mohammad said at a press briefing on Tuesday that Saidur was arrested on Monday. Saidur took over after the execution of JMB chief Shaikh Abdur Rahman. Seven policemen were injured in a grenade attack on Sunday night while raiding a hideout of another outlawed militant organisation Harkat-ul-Jihad-al Islami, Bangladesh in Jurain. Ten grenades were recovered after an attack on policemen during the raid on a flat. Police also arrested Siddiqur Rahman and said he was a member of the military winfg of harkat-ul-Jihad-al-Islami, Bangladesh Banned over the years, the JMB and several other Islamist groups aim to turn Bangladesh into a Dharia state, launching bomb attacks and killing lawyers, judges, police and government officials. Militants launched a countrywide series of bombings in Aug 2005 and are believed to have stages a grenade attack in Aug 21m 2004 that killed 23 people at an Awami League rally addressed by prime minister Sheikh Hasina. Hasina, then the opposition leader, escaped with partial hearing loss. The Islamists kept a low profile after Shaikh Rahman, military wing chief Siddiqur Rahman alias Bangla Bhai and four other JMB leaders were executed in March 2007. But they started regrouping after Hasina took office in January 2009. Intelligence reports say they were planning an offensive soon as the government started a fresh sweep against them. 
